whereas.text:
Whereas the Stonewall Inn was a bar primarily patronized by a diverse cross-section of the lesbian,
			 gay, bisexual, and transgender community and it became a very popular
			 institution;

Whereas, on June 28, 1970, thousands of lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender Americans took part
			 in the Christopher Street Liberation Day march from Greenwich Village to
			 Central Park to mark the first anniversary of Stonewall;

Whereas in 1999, the building at 51–53 Christopher Street that used to be the Stonewall Inn,
			 Christopher Park, and the immediately surrounding area were listed on the
			 National Register of Historic Places;

Whereas in 2000, the building at 51–53 Christopher Street that used to be the Stonewall Inn,
			 Christopher Park, and the immediately surrounding area were listed as a
			 National Historic Landmark;
